  "title": "An Unscrupulous Undertaking: Ominous Forecast",
  "summary": "On a rain-slick landing pad, the agent Elias greets the newly minted Captain Nastaran Zohreh, handing her command of a job moving roughly 650 tons -- 5,000 units -- aboard the Dreadnaught Edean's Ferry. Nastaran, wary and prickly, takes the datapad and immediately pushes back, demanding the spiceheads be removed from her crew and bristling at being saddled with smugglers she did not choose, including Mr. Drell and Mrs. Axelon. Elias coolly deflects her demands, questions what leverage she imagines she has, and frames the assignment as a simple blue-milk run, forgiving her sharp tone. As Nastaran boards the shuttle, the Falleen Lorda Nasiri Gejalli arrives, and the two men confirm their arrangement while Nasiri orders fresh corpses cleared from the pad with a careless wave. Elias finally reveals that in a few weeks he will be known as Alastar Tritarian, shaking Nasiri's hand on a deal whose ominous undertones promise the simple job is anything but.",
